titleStmt.title: Newes from Holland: of the entertainment of the Queenes Most Excellent Maiestie of Great Britaine, the young Princesse Marie, the prince and princesse of Orange, with the young prince their sonne, and most part of the nobility at Amsterdam; invited thither by the lords estates of that city: where in a barge they were conveyed into the city by divers living swans fastned to her barge; with divers triumphs both by water and land. Also divers other remarkable passages from Liepsich, Erford, Collen, Wessell, and divers other places.
